# Testing

Full guide: [docs/TESTING.md](../../docs/TESTING.md).

## Layout

- All tests live under top-level `test/`, organized by type: `test/unit`,
  `test/functional`, `test/e2e`. Tests are never colocated with source.
- `test/unit/` mirrors `src/` (a test for `src/lib/foo.ts` →
  `test/unit/lib/foo.test.ts`). Component tests → `test/unit/components/`,
  hooks → `test/unit/hooks/`.
- Import source via the `@/` alias, never relative `../../src` paths.
- Component/hook suites opt into jsdom with a top-of-file
  `// @vitest-environment jsdom` docblock. Use `renderWithQuery` /
  `renderHookWithQuery` from `test/helpers.tsx` for React Query code.

## Linting: no inline `eslint-disable` in tests

Do **not** litter test files with `eslint-disable` comments. If a lint rule is
inappropriate for test code, relax it once in the `hardcore/tests` override
block in [eslint.config.mjs](../../eslint.config.mjs) (scoped to `TEST_FILES`)
so every test benefits and the intent is recorded in one place.

```js
// ❌ BAD — inline disable scattered across test files
// eslint-disable-next-line @microsoft/sdl/no-insecure-url
vi.stubEnv("BASE_API_HOSTNAME", "http://api.example.com");

// ✅ GOOD — relax the rule for all tests in eslint.config.mjs › hardcore/tests
"@microsoft/sdl/no-insecure-url": OFF,
```

This preference is test-scoped: source files may still carry a narrowly-scoped
disable when a rule genuinely doesn't fit a specific line.

## Coverage ratchet

Coverage thresholds in `vitest.config.ts` are floored to current coverage.
When you add meaningful tests, raise them so coverage can't backslide.
